  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Uganda population movement 2016 (South Sudan Crisis)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A resurgence of violence in South Sudan in July 2016 has led to almost 200 000 fleeing into Uganda. Several new camps have been established to deal with the influx but these are struggling with a lack of water sanitation and health facilities. An outbreak of cholera in one camp in northern Uganda has led to widespread fears of further outbreaks especially during the rainy season (July - October). Uganda Red Cross have been tasked with providing water sanitation and other services at Bidibidi camp near Yumbe. IFRC have launched an appeal to support this.</narrative>
  </description>
